article.headline: Washington 65, South Carolina 53
article.story:
SEATTLE (AP) -- Reserve Dominique Banks scored 12 points and
Kayla Burt returned to action for the first time in almost two
years as Washington defeated South Carolina 65-53 Sunday afternoon.

In the night cap of the WBCA Classic, Washington used a 21-0 run
midway through the second half in building a 51-38 lead. Breanne
Watson scored eight points during the run, and Burt hit a three
pointer for her first field goal. The Gamecocks went almost 11
minutes without a field goal in the second half.

Burt scored 12 points in returning to action for the first time
since December 2002 when she went into cardiac arrest. This summer,
she was medically cleared to play basketball again, but with a
defibrillator implanted into her chest.

Lauren Simms scored 12 points to lead South Carolina, which has
dropped two straight season openers, losing last year to Clemson.

South Carolina led at the half 29-24 behind tough defensive
pressure. The Gamecocks held the Huskies to just 26 percent
shooting from the field. Washington wasn't any better when the shot
was uncontested, going only five-of-10 from the line in the first
half.

Earlier Sunday, 14th-ranked Minnesota defeated UNLV 77-69.
